social_posts.post_text:
To make my stance on this topic clear, this is about mass theft of copyrighted material by a wide range of artists over their lifetimes and using that material to train AI to mimic them FOR PROFIT. I do not support the use of this technology until artists are compensated for the unauthorized use of their copyrighted work and laws are passed to further protect them.

Artists spend years of their lives developing their own personal style and quality of work, and the majority of that development and hard work is unpaid, invisible labor. An artist’s personal style is developed based on their own experiences, choices, worldview, skillset, mistakes, and a LOT of time. When these images are stolen and used to train AI models, those years of hard work and personal input are also stolen without royalties or credit. The AI user ultimately profits from the artist’s labor.

Now is the time to organize and collectively defend artists’ rights. You can be excited for the opportunity this new technology brings while also pushing for ethical use and legislation of AI. Non-artists, this will soon impact everything you interact with and consume as well as the use of your own data - we should all be worried about the non-consensual data scraping that is occurring here.

@conceptartassociation has started a GoFundMe that outlines tangible steps they will be taking to educate government officials and policymakers in Washington about this issue. Please consider supporting this effort to ensure this technology is utilized in an ethical way without misuse of artists’ IP. The GoFundMe link is in my bio. 

A personal aside to anyone wanting to create art: current use of this technology erases the most valuable part of the creative journey: individual growth and exploration. There is immense value in the problem solving and discovery of arriving at an answer. Do not rob yourself of this journey and growth, it is the best part of being an artist. If you only value the destination and output, you will find yourself (and the content you consume) empty.

Shout out to @kortizart @jonlamart @conceptartassociation and many others for being at the frontlines of this issue.

Friends! Jan 6, come out and see some beautiful artwork by my inspiring art heroes and incredibly attractive friends @tanyawischerath and @dawndundundun in our group show Outlandish at @wavecollectivespace

I’ll be contributing a large body of recent work featuring small gouache paintings of Bay Area landscapes, still life paintings, and color studies. Most of the work will be priced under $300, making this a perfect show to show some support for your local artists and art collectives. We’ll have a performance by @omgkatmarie at the opening party. I’m honored and inspired to share space with these incredible artists, hope to see you all there!

#queerart #outlandish #galleryshow
